<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-672-339  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 672 339.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Federal Computer Week  April 10 1989 v3 n15 p11(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Air Force wraps up first phase of graphics upgrade. (at AirDefense Operations Center)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Brewin, Bob.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Air Force completes the initial phase of its five-phase $200million upgrade of Air Defense Operations Center graphics systemsand terminals.andP;  The upgrade project, code-named Granite Sentry,uses mostly commercial hardware and software and runs over 125,000lines of Ada code.andP;  The Air Force Electronic Systems Div acted asprime contractor; DEC subcontracted for hardware and the Air ForceSpace Command subcontracted as software developer.andP;  The initialphase provides new displays for tracking potential cruise missileand bomber attacks to the North American Air Defense Command inCheyenne Mountain, CO. Space Command programmers are now at workon the second phase, which will provide better missile warningdisplays for the command post.andP;  The Ada code links commercialsoftware with the Graphical Kernel System display software thattakes incoming messages and processes them for display on multipleterminals.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     United States. Air ForceUpgradingGraphics SystemsTerminalsDefense ContractsDisplaysUnited States. Air Defense Operations Center.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>